\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 They had a heavy supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Yes. And the mushrooms - oh I loved the mushrooms, but I was in bed
 but we - we got mushrooms like - the next day. Oh, my brother and I would get two big basket fulls, all fresh white mushrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Did your mother and father have a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12191358\charrsid8598525 lot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525  of visitors coming in like that for an evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Well - not a lot, it was - it w
as just a friend of hers, not a relation, and - I think she - must have - he never ever married her but she went with my uncle you see. He never married anybody to tell you the truth. And neither did she, they're both away now of course. Well they used to
 
come up together, and this - other - his name was Nughes, and - he - was a - he photo - done a lot of photo - photographs and he used to bring the magic lantern. And then there would perhaps be a gardener come from some other big house or something like t
hat. But it was - they weren't - noisy - just to have your supper, and game and dominoes. They used to like the dominoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Did your mother and father ever go out at nights and visit other people?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Oh just at Christmastime. We all used to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 They wouldn't go and leave you behind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 
Oh no, no. No. And - no, they never - of course there wasn't the - facilities to do that then, your mother was all - were always busy. There were no - she used to go out - maybe in an afternoon to the womens guil
d or something like that, that they called the mothers meetings then. And leave us with my father, and then - my father, if there was any circuses - or processions in the town which - used to be - my father always took us over - to the town to see it. And
 took us to the circus, we went to the circus.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Your mother didn't have friends that she went and visited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 
Yes, she went to meetings and go to my granny's I suppose and - maybe - have a chat with - people she knew, everybody knew everybody then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 You say that you went to your granny's on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Oh yes. Yes, a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 How about your other granny, did you see much of her?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 
There were no other - we only had the one. Aye. My father's - mother had died, I never knew her. No. No, on
ly had the one. And my mother used to say she was the best mother-in-law in the world. Aye. I - I told you the - one about my mother saying - if ever you're spared - to have a house or home of your own, don't deal all in the one shop. Go about. And she sa
y
s, many times she used to tell me she says, you know - she says, you had plenty of food, but I just used to wonder what I was going to have for our dinner the next day. And she says, there wouldn't have been much money left. She says, your - grandma came 
i
n - she must have read my thoughts and she handed me a sovereign. She said, I never asked her for anything in my life. And she came up, but she knew my mother - you know, looked after us all, and she would give her a sovereign. She says, she must have rea
d my thoughts. So you see she was a - a - a great granny she was, you know, a good granny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Did you go and visit her apart from a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 
She never gave money to my father, she always gave it to my mother. Oh she never gave it to her son.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Gave it to the one who was doing the spending?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 
Doing the - doing the spending. And she says, you know, she says, I think God heard my prayer. But she was - she worried, you know, and we had plenty, we weren't - we weren't - we weren't well off buy we we
re comfortable you know, we got - we didn't get a lot of grandeur or anything but we were always clean and tidy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 And well fed by the sound of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Ah.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Did you go down and see your granny through the week as well?
