Oh yes. Oh yes, we had to make that marriage, yes. And he - he wasn't a man that went and left me, you know, in places 
and - sat in the mess all the time. If he went to anything oh I was there too but - not in - every evening, he used to go and have his - his - pint or whatever he wanted, and - but in these country - you're always in a country place, back of beyond, but t
h
ese places - they more enjoy a social life there than there was in towns. You had clubs, you had - Conservatives, you had the British Legion, you had - Conserv - Conservative then the working men's club where the wifes could go but you weren't allowed in 
t
he bar or anything like that, and they used to have concerts of professionals from London, they'd - entertainment we had, then we would have - some of the Conservative clubs and - and - that, we had - competitions, baking competitions, different things li
ke that, and garden parties and had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12191358\charrsid8598525 committee}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525  and that.
