What sort of place in the community did like the minister and the doctor take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Did you think of them as one of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Well - no, you looked up to them that they were the 
- they were a wee bit above you, the doctors - and the ministers, but - they put you at your ease, now the doctors - you had your doctor, your family doctor, and my - my mother's was Doctor Grey, and - you know - you got your bill and - and he'd - he'd co
me, and perhaps it would be about four and sixpence, for all the times that he - and that was paid, and - the doctor would come whether you paid or not in these days. May a doctor never got his bill paid, I don't know how they lived - how they lived.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 They must have made it off the well off people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 
Well they must have done, because - many a doctor never sent his bill in to a person that - was down and out. My mother maybe was short of money but she never was - down and out because the wage wasn't 
big and she spent it and spent it on us and - and bought food. She never saved anything for she couldn't. Had to feed us all. But my father never kept money - although he - did like his - sort of whisky or beer or whatever it was, it was just his pocket m
oney, and you could buy a lot then, he never kept money off my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Did your mother ever join any clubs for saving money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Well, the only thing was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Did she have any insurance or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 They had - no, she had what was t
he Free Gardeners - Society, and paid so much a week into that, and - father was ill he got so much off it. And then when this - national health came you know, she's still paying in to the Free Gardeners, you got so much money back out of it because it wo
und up then. He got so - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12077264\charrsid8598525 tendency}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 
 - they divided the money all up and every - everyone that was a member of that - it was - put out to them. I remember going paying that - Free Gardeners, it was the Free Gardeners - Insurance So - Society, I don't, I think 
if you died you got so much out of it too. Aye, that was the only thing - my mother never had - had us insured until we were very - we were older. She never bothered about - insurance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 After you'd been in Glasgow Street you moved to Queensbury Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 You were in rented houses all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Oh yes, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Did you ever have any trouble with landlords?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 No. You - your rent was paid six monthly. It wasn't paid weekly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 In Advance,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Well I don't know whether it
 was in advance or not, but you paid your rent and your rates all at once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 That must have been a fair whack?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 
It was a fair whack, it was about six pound ten a half year. But you know my mother used to belong to the Co-op and the dividends were 
big. Used to get about three and six in the pound then, and that dividend - would have helped to pay her rent. See? Uh huh. Yes, well that's - well of course when you were - when they was in the serve - in the gardners service up here you - you'l no rent 
t
o pay like. No, he got - he had the free hours. But - when we were in the rented houses - I think it came to about six pound ten, every half year. Well - you'd that put always but I don't know how my mother done at all to tell you the truth, I don't think
 I ever bothered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 I suppose as you children got older she would have something coming in?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 
Oh yes, she had - yes, she had to and then - my grandfather - well it was - my father's stepfather but he's awfully good to us children in the way of everyt
hing, gave my mother money to go to the sale and get the boots or shoes or - and he'd maybe buy us a coat or something like that. We always seemed to be lucky - in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Lucky with your relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Aye. And my mother of course - we were made 
to look after our clothes that you didn't get so many, you had to look after them. You had your - you had your weekday clothes and you had your Sunday clothes, and you just had to look after them. Make them last. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 When you were working did you buy your own clothes then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 
Oh yes, well - yes, sometimes I did - oh yes, I did - because I used to - buy my own stockings and things like that, 'cos mother - I - I remember mother saying if I was buying them I wouldn't be buying these things. Of cours
e just like all the rest, well there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12077264\charrsid8598525 were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525  the clogs up }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12077264\charrsid8598525 from here}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 
, you know, the - lisle - stockings, oh yes used to have our pocket money and save a bit of it. And - and we always had our banks to put - wee bit of money in, and shaking it to see how much y
ou had. Getting a knife to pick it out. When your mother wasnae looking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Did you ever get away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Oh yes, used to go to - no, we - no holidays now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Saving up for things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Yes, I used to go to - you know, round about, differ
ent places, no far away - later on like when - I was married and that I had holidays, but before that - maybe go up to Glasgow - but you wouldn't stay, just for the day there. Or you'd go to some of your friends in the country. Used to be fine fun going t
here. Went for about a week or so. And - it was farms you know we were on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 
Did you sort of take turns, you would go and visit somebody on a farm and they would come and visit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Well, there was - wasn't a visit into the town, they never got in
to the town these country people, it was only - every six month they got their pay. Six months. Oh - oh - I don't know, the - they just seemed to - holidays }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12077264\charrsid8598525 
weren't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525  - there weren't the brochures and things like that, they would only before the big people, 
the millionaires in these days. They had their cruises. But we didn't have a life like, that. Didn't bother. Didn't bother me. I used to go maybe to Carlisle for a day and Glasgow for a day. And - then to a seaside place for the day. I enjoyed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Did you go with your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Yes. With friends as you got older. Uh huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Were there ever policemen round about where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 
Oh yes. Knew all the policemen. They were friendly, oh they were friendly, same when I was in the shop I knew all the policemen, I knew all the policemen in the town, they knew me too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 By coming into the shop,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 
Yes, coming into the shop. There was one, he was talking about how - how - a chum and I, I don't - I can't remember it but - since I've been in this
 house I was going up Buccleugh Street one day, and - I knew this other fellow - and I said hello to him and he was talking to a man, he was lame, this man had a stick, and - he said - he said, Netty come here, he says, this - somebody wants to meet you. 
A
nd I went back, I said - he said, don't you know me? No. I said, no. He says, don't you remember - Lockett the policeman? I said, no - I don't know, I says, don't know, I says, are - are you him? He says, yes, he says, you remember the day that you and yo
u
r chum Jenny Allen came up the Fishers Lodge and - another policeman and I were in the River Nith bathing and you hid our clothes? I says - I says, I don't remember it. He says, you did, he says, when we came out we couldn't find our clothes. I said, wher
e did you find them? He says, stuck in a hedge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12077264\charrsid8598525 Obviously}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525  you weren't afraid of the police then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 
No. We had gone up the Fishers Lodge for a walk and they were - in the water and they shouted at us, and we seen their clothes and we went and hid th
em and walked away, went away and left them, don't remember it, but he remembered it. We had a good laugh. But I says, I don't really remember doing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Obviously you were on good terms with them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Oh dear, oh aye, you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Your mother never sort of threatened you that if you didn't behave -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 
No, no. Oh no. No, no. I knew the - I knew - not when I was little, you knew the police, you just knew you didn't have to - didn't have to do anything - that required the police. However - I knew them
 more when I was in the shop, 'cos they were always - there or thereabout. I don't know, a different opinion of police now I don't know, the world's all different now as it was in the - in these days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16721817 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Very much changed isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11304503 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14574712\charrsid8598525 Very much changed. There's more crime - now than there was then. I think.

\par }}